x4freetext: Low-Lying Excited States of 70Ga and 72Ga Populated in
Thermal-Neutron Capture.
Constructed the decay scheme of low-lying
states in 70Ga and 72Ga.
Determined the neutron binding energies 7651(1) keV
for 70Ga and 6519(1) keV for 72Ga.
IS+VM

x4headers.headerHelp: Dummy incident proj. energy, for broad spectrum

x4codes.hlp: Argonne National Laboratory, Argonne, IL, United States of America

x4freetext: Argonne CP-5 reseach reactor tangential
through-tube facility which allows highly collimated
beam of gamma rays emitted by target to emerge from
reactor tube. Low-energy transitions strongly
attenuated in the neutron shielding material.
Reactor core with a thermal-neutron flux ~3.E+13
neutrons/cm2/s at the sample position.
Slab of borated polyethylene placed between target and
detector in order to suppress thermal- and epithermal-
neutron flux and to limit counting rate in detector
to a tolerable range (~2000 counts/sec).
Reactor spectrum with cadmium ratio ~7.
Powder oxide Ga2O3 samples, enriched to 99.75% in
69Ga, weighing 4.0 g, encapsulated in high-purity
graphite sample holders and installed at center of
tangential through-tube facility.
Results obtained from 2 runs lasting 42 h.
Pair-spectrometer results obtained after 65-h running
time.
4-cm3 Ge(Li) spectrometer with energy resolution
width of ~6 keV at 6-MeV deposited energy used in
singles gamma-ray spectroscopy
. Above Ge(Li) detector used as central detector
with two 4x4-in NaI(T1) side crystals mounted 180
degrees apart.
Energy calibration based on the carbon ground-state
neutron-capture gamma-ray at 4945.46(17) keV, present
due to graphite sample holder.
Relative detection efficiency for double-escape peaks
determined empirically as a function of gamma-ray
energy using nitrogen neutron-capture gamma-ray
spectrum and known relative intensities of its
various components.
Relative intensities normalized to 6391-keV line
which was arbitrarily taken as 3.03 photons per
100 neutron captures. Value obtained by Rasmussen
et al. (unpublished, MIT) for absolute intensity of
the same line in natural gallium.
Minimization program used for analyzing spectra by
fitting the peaks with a Gaussian line shape plus a
linear background.
Due to spectral complexities and other uncertainties
encountered for transitions energies < 4.5 MeV,
capture gamma-ray spectra below this energy were
not analyzed in detail.
Uncertainties in gamma-ray energies.

x4code.headerHelp: Error in value of quantity, defined under ERR-ANALYS

x4freetext: Uncertainties of line intensities includes
~15% uncertainty in line intensities in nitrogen used
in to determine relative double-escape-peak detector
efficiences of Ge(Li) detector.
Doubtful line.
Data taken from Table I of reference.

beam facility.
Highly collimated external beam of thermal
neutrons.

33-mg sample of Ga metal enriched to 99.61% in 71Ga.
20-cm3 Ge(Li) spectrometer with energy resolutio
width of 2.6 keV at 1.3-MeV deposited energy.
Energies determined relative to gamma-rays at
121.970(30) and 661.635(17) keV from decay of 57Co and
Cs137, respectively.
Relative intensities normalized to 145.09-keV line,
taken as 100.
